  "title": "FortiAnalyzer could potentially be used in NTP amplification attacks",
  "summary": "An insufficient control of network message volume (CWE-406) vulnerability in FortiAnalyzer may allow an unauthenticated remote attacker to perform NTP amplification attacks (thereby causing reflected denial of service on arbitrary targets) via sending specially crafted mode 6 queries to the FortiAnalyzer built-in NTP server.",
